free: #e There is (a story I will) tell.
#e Long time ago, there was a boy.
#c 很久以前有一個男孩子。
#e Since his childhood, there has been a girl whom he gets together with in the village.
#c 從他小時候，有一個女孩子在村子裡一直跟他一起。
#e The girl, when she grows flowers, she feels happy.
#c 那女孩，當她種花時，他覺得快樂。
#e Therefore, she intends to grow (flowers) everywhere all over the whole village.
#c 因此，她想在村子裡到處種滿花。
#e (Then,) just like this, the boy and the girl grew up.
#c (後來)就這樣，男孩和女孩長大了。
#e Unexpectedly, the boy loved the girl.
#c 竟然男孩喜歡上了女孩。
#e One time, they two walked together to the hill and played.
#c 有一次他們兩個一起去山上玩。
#e The boy sang and picked one flower, the flower that the girl liked.
#c 男孩唱歌，並且摘了一朵花，一朵那女孩喜歡的花。
#e (He) sang a song which was loved by the girl, and picked a flower which was loved by the girl.
#c 他唱了一首女孩喜歡的歌，摘了一朵女孩喜歡的花。
#e He would intend to give (it) to the girl, and would intend to ask for the girl's love.
#c 他想要把（花）給女孩，希望女孩喜歡他。
#e Unexpectedly, at that time, a girl was seen crying beside the river.
#c 突然，這時候看到一個女孩在河邊哭。
#e (he found out that) The girl who cried was (originally) washing clothes.
#c 原來那女孩本來在洗衣服。
#e One of the clothes which are washed drifted away.
#e I would like to wear the dress which drifted away when we hold the ceremony tomorrow.
#c 我想要在明天的祭典穿那件漂走的衣服。
#e The boy helped (the girl) and got the clothes drifting away, and gave (it) back to the girl.
#c 那男孩幫助（那女孩）拿回漂走的衣服，並且還給了那女孩。
#e It's seen ... The boy who helped got her clothes.
#c 就看到...來幫助的男孩幫忙拿她的衣服。
#e Unexpectedly, the girl liked this boy very much.
#c 出其不意的那女孩非常喜歡這個男孩。
#e But, as for the boy, the one who washes clothes is not the girl whom is loved by him.
#c 但是對那個男孩而言，洗衣服的那個女孩不是他喜歡的。
#e The one whom the boy liked was the one who growed flowers.
#c 男孩喜歡的那個是種花的。
